Question: In converting a bipolar transistor's small-signal equivalent circuit from the intrinsic T-model to the π-model, which of the following expressions correctly describes how the intrinsic π-model transconductance g_{\mathrm{m}} depends on the T-model parameters?

A. g_{\mathrm{m}} = \alpha_{0} \sqrt{\left(1/r_{\pi}\right)^2 + (\omega C_{\pi})^2} / \sqrt{1 + (\omega \tau_{\pi})^2}

B. g_{\mathrm{m}} = \alpha_{0} \sqrt{\left(1/r_{\mathrm{e}}\right)^2 + (\omega C_{\mathrm{e}})^2} / \sqrt{1 + (\omega \tau_{\alpha})^2}

C. g_{\mathrm{m}} = \alpha_{0} \left(1/r_{\mathrm{e}} + \omega C_{\mathrm{e}}\right) / \left(1 + \omega \tau_{\alpha}\right)

D. g_{\mathrm{m}} = \alpha_{0} / \left(r_{\mathrm{e}} + 1/(\omega C_{\mathrm{e}})\right) \times \sqrt{1 + (\omega \tau_{\alpha})^{2}}
